#From the #1085 meta-list: Fade Away (no symptom given).
#Each creature's controller sacrifices a permanent unless they pay
#{1}: with no mana left, the caster's own bears must be sacrificed.
# https://github.com/WagicProject/wagic/issues/1085
[INIT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
inplay:grizzly bears
hand:fade away
manapool:{2}{U}
[PLAYER2]
[DO]
fade away
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
choice 0
grizzly bears
goto secondmain
goto secondmain
[ASSERT]
SECONDMAIN
[PLAYER1]
graveyard:fade away,grizzly bears
[PLAYER2]
[END]
#UPDATE 2026-06-11 pay[[ round: the grant now carries its full text (engine
#fix landed - nim/pendrell pass) and the pay menu APPEARS: choice 0 on the
#unaffordable pay HANGS (known trap), choice 1 reaches the decline but its
#"sacrifice notaTarget(*|mybattlefield)" auto-pick resolves choosing nothing
#(the purging_scythe trigger-context notaTarget family). Park stands on that
#narrower layer.
